name: Ordinal

values.name: ordinal
values.comment:
Convert an integer into an English ordinal number string (like `"4th"`).

    ordinal 42 == "42nd"
    ordinal 0 == "0th"
    ordinal (-1) == "-1st"

values.name: ordinalSuffix
values.comment:
Get the English ordinal suffix (st/nd/rd/th) for a given integer.

    ordinalSuffix 42 == "nd"
    ordinalSuffix 0 == "th"
    ordinalSuffix (-1) == "st"
